item.title: My run server doesnt work :(
item.dc:creator: @bryanc Bryanc
item.description:
@bryanc wrote:

Linksbro:

Have you set your enviroment varibles?

Fail , you don’t get that error if you don’t have environment variables set.

Project Evolution:

1. You did’nt set you variables right, or not even at all.

Fail x2, you don’t get that error if you don’t have environment variables set.

[hr]

You probably have a process running in the background of the server. If you have windows, press ctrl + alt + delete and goto the processes tab. Close the java.exe if there is one, then try running again. If that doesn’t work then try to reboot you’re computer and try again. It’s because a server is already running on port 43594.
